8888contact-us/\">online inquiry</a>, send an e-mail to <a href=\"mailto:admissions@eastsidecommunityschool.org?subject=Admissions Inquiry\">admissions@eastsidecommunityschool.org</a>, or call (425) 598-2914, and share with us the following information:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Full name</li>\r\n 	<li>E-mail address</li>\r\n 	<li>Phone number</li>\r\n 	<li>Child’s age</li>\r\n 	<li>Program you are inquiring about (Early Childhood or one of the Grades)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe can then send you information about our school and programs, and keep you informed about important admission events and dates.\r\n<h2>2. Attend an Open House or School Tour</h2>\r\nCheck the dates and times of scheduled <a href=\"http://localhost:8888admissions-open-houses-tours/\">Open Houses and Tours</a>.\r\n\r\nIf you are not able to attend these scheduled events, we may be able to offer you an alternative date and time. Please <a href=\"http://localhost:8888contact-us/\">contact us</a> to schedule.\r\n<h2>3. Submit Application Form and Pay Application Fee</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong><em>FOR APPLICATION TO THE CURRENT SCHOOL YEAR, 2018-2019:</em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Please complete the <a class=\"pdfFormDownload\" href=\"http://localhost:8888learn/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Admission18-19_Application-Form.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Application Form</a>, and email it to <a href=\"mailto:admissions@eastsidecommunityschool.org?subject=Application\">admissions@eastsidecommunityschool.org</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Please pay the non-refundable Application Fee by Paypal or by check payable to <em>Eastside Community School</em>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign=\"top\">\r\n<td><strong>Early Childhood and Grades 1-8</strong>\r\n\r\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\"><input name=\"cmd\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"_s-xclick\" />\r\n\r\n<input name=\"hosted_button_id\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"J4AZVRVBKMZVC\" />\r\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%;\"><input name=\"on0\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"Application and Enrollment Fees\" />Application and Enrollment Fees</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><select name=\"os0\">\r\n<option value=\"Application Fee\">Application Fee $75.00 USD</option>\r\n<option value=\"Enrollment Fee - New Families\">Enrollment Fee - New Families $750.00 USD</option>\r\n<option value=\"Enrollment Fee - New Families (Applying for Financial Aid)\">Enrollment Fee - New Families (Applying for Financial Aid) $500.00 USD</option>\r\n<option value=\"Reinrollment Fee - Current Families\">Reinrollment Fee - Current Families $200.00 USD</option>\r\n</select></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<input name=\"currency_code\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"USD\" />\r\n\r\n<input alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" name=\"submit\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_paynowCC_LG.gif\" type=\"image\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" />\r\n\r\n</form></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%;\"><strong>Parent & Child</strong>\r\n\r\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\"><input name=\"cmd\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"_s-xclick\" />\r\n\r\n<input name=\"hosted_button_id\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"GY7P7ZRP4LQ9Y\" />\r\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><input name=\"on0\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"Tuition\" />Tuition</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><select name=\"os0\">\r\n<option value=\"Tuesday - Winter/Spring Session\">Tuesday - Winter/Spring Session $800.00 USD</option>\r\n<option value=\"Thursday - Winter/Spring Session\">Thursday - Winter/Spring Session $320.00 USD</option>\r\n</select></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<input name=\"currency_code\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"USD\" />\r\n\r\n<input alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" name=\"submit\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_paynowCC_LG.gif\" type=\"image\" />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" />\r\n\r\n</form></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong><em>FOR APPLICATION TO THE NEXT SCHOOL YEAR, 2019-2020:</em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Please click <a href=\"https://mytads.com/a/eastside\">here</a> to complete the application via TADS, an online web-based system.</li>\r\n 	<li>This process will need to be done for each child you wish to enroll.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>4. Request Teacher Questionnaire and Transcripts</h2>\r\nIf your child is currently attending another program, please submit a Transcripts Request (Grades 1-8 only), and Teacher Questionnaire to the school your child is attending. The Transcripts and Teacher Questionnaire must be submitted directly from the current school to Eastside Community School.\r\n<h2>5. Family Interview with Eastside Community School Faculty</h2>\r\nOnce we have received your Application Form, Teacher Questionnaire, Transcripts (if applicable), and Application Fee, we will contact you for a Family Interview with faculty.\r\n<h2>6. Schedule a Visit (Grades Only)</h2>\r\nFollowing a successful Family Interview, eligible applicants to grades 2-8 will have an opportunity to schedule a visit (up to three days), and attend classes with their prospective teacher and peers.\r\n<h2>7. Acceptance Notifications</h2>\r\nAcceptance notifications will be emailed within one week of the Family Interview and/or visit.\r\n<h2>8. Apply for Financial Aid</h2>\r\nIf you wish to apply for Financial Aid please contact <a href=\"mailto:admissions@eastsidecommunityschool.org?subject=Financial Aid Inquiry\">admissions@eastsidecommunityschool.org</a>\r\n<h2>9. Complete Enrollment Packet, Pay Deposit and Enrollment Fee</h2>\r\nA completed Enrollment Packet, Enrollment Fee, and Tuition Deposit, are due within 10 business days of the date on the Enrollment Agreement.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://get.adobe.com/reader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Get Adobe Reader</a>\r\n\r\nTo use fill-able PDF forms, please save the form on your computer, and open in Adobe Reader.\r\n\r\n<!--In January 2016, Three Cedars Waldorf School merged with Seattle Waldorf School, and we have combined our admission process. To find more information about the application process for either campus, <a href=\"http://www.seattlewaldorf.org/admissions/application-process/\">please click here.</a>-->\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n'),(38227,9318,'_thumbnail_id','9327'),(7207,4187,'_edit_last','11'),(1557,2477,'layout',''),(1558,2477,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','34ceb3230b'),(1559,2477,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Admissions'),(1560,2477,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1561,2477,'sidebar','Admissions'),(1562,2477,'header','yes'),(1563,2477,'footer',''),(1564,2477,'_edit_lock','1552290289:11'),(1565,2478,'_edit_last','11'),(1566,2478,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1567,2478,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(38846,9982,'_dp_original','2478'),(38847,9982,'_edit_lock','1552280438:11'),(38848,2478,'classic-editor-remember','classic-editor'),(38849,2478,'_avia_builder_shortcode_tree','a:8:{i:0;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:12:\"av_textblock\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:0;}i:1;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:8:\"av_table\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:1;}i:2;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:12:\"av_textblock\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:2;}i:3;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:8:\"av_table\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:3;}i:4;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:12:\"av_textblock\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:4;}i:5;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:8:\"av_table\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:5;}i:6;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:12:\"av_textblock\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:6;}i:7;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:19:\"av_toggle_container\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:7;}}'),(38477,9625,'_wp_attached_file','2018/06/Employment-Application-Form.pdf'),(33483,8158,'_EventOrigin','events-calendar'),(33484,8158,'_edit_lock','1445527500:6'),(33485,8158,'_edit_last','6'),(33486,8158,'_EventShowMapLink',''),(33487,8158,'_EventShowMap',''),(33488,8158,'_EventStartDate','2015-10-26 09:30:00'),(33489,8158,'_EventEndDate','2015-10-26 10:00:00'),(24647,2478,'header_transparency',''),(24648,2478,'_avia_hide_featured_image','0'),(1569,2478,'layout',''),(1570,2478,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','74834e1dbc'),(1571,2478,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Admissions'),(1572,2478,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1573,2478,'sidebar','Admissions'),(1574,2478,'header','yes'),(1575,2478,'footer',''),(1576,2478,'_edit_lock','1552280868:11'),(1577,2479,'_edit_last','11'),(1578,2479,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1579,2479,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(25944,2479,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Financial Aid</h1>\r\nEastside Community School (ECS) believes that any qualified student who can benefit from attending ECS should not refrain from applying for admission solely due to potential lack of financial resources. To the extent that our funds permit, financial aid is available to qualified students whose parents demonstrate financial need through the financial aid application process.\r\n\r\nEastside Community School uses TADS, a web-based system, for the financial aid application process. Review the <a href=\"http://localhost:8888learn/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Financial-Aid-Application-Instructions.docx\">Financial Aid Application Instructions</a> document and click <a href=\"https://www.mytads.com/\">here</a> to begin the application process.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>New families for the 2018-2019 school year</strong> should indicate a request for financial aid by checking the appropriate box on the Enrollment Agreement. The school will contact you with further instructions.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Returning families for the 2019-2020 school year</strong> should complete the TADS financial aid application by 2/25/2019.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>New families for the 2019-2020 school year</strong> should begin the TADS financial aid application upon acceptance to Eastside Community School and complete the application as soon as possible.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_hr class=\'default\' height=\'50\' shadow=\'no-shadow\' position=\'center\' custom_border=\'av-border-thin\' custom_width=\'50px\' custom_border_color=\'\' custom_margin_top=\'30px\' custom_margin_bottom=\'30px\' icon_select=\'yes\' custom_icon_color=\'\' icon=\'ue808\']\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Questions</h1>\r\nIf you have questions about how to fill out the application, look first at the TADS \"Help\" tab on the right side of their webpage, or contact TADS directly.\r\n\r\nIf you have questions about the overall process, contact Janine Cleland by sending an <a href=\"mailto:FinancialAid@eastsidecommunityschool.org\">email</a> or calling 425-598-2914.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_toggle_container initial=\'1\' mode=\'toggle\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'What is financial aid? \' tags=\'\']\r\n<p class=\"Compact\">Financial aid provides need-based assistance for tuition to students who qualify through the financial aid application process. Financial need is defined as the difference between a family’s resources and ability to contribute toward the cost of education and the cost of tuition. All awards are made in the form of grants, which are not repaid to the school.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Compact\">ECS uses TADS Financial Aid Assessment (TADS FA) as the foundation for the financial aid process. TADS FA relies upon a standard methodology to assess the resources available to a family to contribute toward a child’s educational expenses.</p>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Should our family apply for financial aid? \' tags=\'\']\r\n<p class=\"Compact\">Eastside Community School, like most independent schools, believes that a family holds primary responsibility for financing their child’s education to the extent they are able. We also believe that families should consider utilizing all available resources before applying for financial aid. We expect that families will take the time to realistically assess their financial situation and determine how much they can afford to pay. With this determination in mind, the family can decide whether or not to apply for aid.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Compact2\">A good rule of thumb is: if in doubt, apply. It costs very little, and because so many factors are considered, it is always worth going through the process. It is important to understand that there is no specific income level at which a family will not qualify for financial aid.</p>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'How much does it cost to apply?\' tags=\'\']\r\n<p class=\"Compact\">When you complete your TADS FA application online, you will be asked to pay $42 regardless of the number of schools to which you apply. TADS FA offers financial assistance for the application fee when a family meets certain established financial criteria. If you meet those criteria, the system will waive the fee when you submit your application.</p>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'How do I start the TADS FA process? \' tags=\'\']\r\nGo to <a href=\"http://www.myTADS.com\">www.myTADS.com</a> and either sign in or create an account.  Then enter the state (WA), city (Bellevue) and school (Eastside Community School) to get started.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'What are the school’s priorities in terms of who receives aid? \' tags=\'\']\r\nFinancial aid is awarded in the following priority order by category of student:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Families currently enrolled at ECS,</li>\r\n 	<li>New students who have been admitted to the school.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition, ECS strives to allocate funds across classes and at levels that help to meet enrollment goals and support socio-economic diversity throughout the school.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'How is our family’s financial need determined? \' tags=\'\']\r\n<p class=\"Compact\">The process of determining a family’s financial need begins with TADS FA processing the information you provide according to a standard methodology to assess the resources your family has available to contribute toward your student’s educational expenses. The result of this evaluation is released to Eastside Community School, as well as to any other schools to which you are applying for aid. You can also request that a copy of this report be sent to you. Some factors that TADS FA takes into consideration include: income (both taxable and nontaxable), assets (home equity, savings, investments, etc.), expenses, indebtedness, family size, age of parents/guardians (to allow for retirement savings), and the number of students attending tuition-charging schools.</p>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'What happens if our child has assets? \' tags=\'\']\r\nThe financial assets that a child has will be taken into consideration by TADS FA. That amount will be divided by the number of years the student has left in school through four-year college and added to the parental contribution for education. The sum of both the parent(s) and the student contributions equals the recommended family contribution for education.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'What happens after TADS FA has completed its evaluation? \' tags=\'\']\r\nThe ECS Financial Aid Committee will review the TADS Report of Family Contribution (RFC) along with any other information we may request from the family. The committee may adjust the TADS suggested family contribution based on information provided by the family, school financial aid policies, and the availability of funds. Your calculated family contribution will then be subtracted from the tuition costs for the year, in order to determine your family’s financial aid grant.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Will our family receive the difference between the cost of tuition and what my Report of Family Contribution says we can contribute? \' tags=\'\']\r\n<p class=\"Compact\">Not entirely. We require that every family contribute financially toward tuition. And, because there is more demand for financial aid than available school funds, we cannot meet 100% of determined need. We hope that by providing support for a substantial percentage of a family’s financial need, more students will be able to attend Eastside Community School.</p>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Who will see the information provide by TADS FA to the school? \' tags=\'\']\r\n<p class=\"Compact\">All records and correspondence regarding financial aid are held in strict confidence. Information will be reviewed only by those persons directly involved in the financial aid decision-making process or in its administration (Business Office staff and the Administrator).</p>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Can you consider our application for financial aid if we have not provided all the information requested? \' tags=\'\']\r\n<p class=\"Compact\">No. Financial aid to a family cannot be awarded if the application is incomplete. We will attempt to advise you if we have not received all materials needed prior to considering your application, to give you an opportunity to submit the remaining materials.\r\nThe sooner you provide all necessary information to complete your application, the sooner ECS can evaluate your need for financial aid.</p>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Do we have other options if our family’s full need is not met? \' tags=\'\']\r\n<p class=\"Compact\">We offer a monthly payment plan that may help make payments easier on your family’s budget. Your banking institution can also provide you with information about low-interest educational loan programs. You should also look for other forms of financial assistance that may be available through your place of employment, community organizations, local foundations or extended family.</p>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'How are my financial status and ability to pay evaluated if I am separated or divorced? \' tags=\'\']\r\nEastside Community School believes that the primary responsibility for paying for a child’s education rests with both parents. Financial aid is not based on the willingness to pay, but on the ability to pay. Therefore, it is the responsibility of all parents/guardians to complete all steps in the application process. In families where one or both parents are remarried or have a domestic partner, their financial information is taken into consideration as well.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'If our child receives financial aid for one year, will our child automatically receive aid each of the following years? \' tags=\'\']\r\n<p class=\"Compact\">No. Family and school circumstances can change from year to year and therefore, we need current and accurate information each year. All families seeking financial aid must reapply each school year.</p>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Are students who receive financial aid treated differently than other students? \' tags=\'\']\r\nNo. Expectations with regard to academic performance, behavior, and all other aspects of school life are the same for all students, regardless of whether the student is receiving financial aid or not.  Furthermore, teachers and staff are not informed of students whose families benefit from financial aid. Please be assured\r\nthat all financial aid matters are handled with the highest level\r\nof discretion.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Will my child’s admission be affected if we apply for financial aid? \' tags=\'\']\r\nNo. Admission decisions and financial aid decisions are made independently. The financial aid team does not complete its review of a financial aid application until the Business Office has been advised that a student will be admitted by the Admissions Committee.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888learn/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/ECS-Financial-Aid-FAQS-TADS-v20190111.pdf\">Download PDF</a> of the FAQs listed above.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n'),(1581,2479,'layout',''),(1582,2479,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','1042bdfa3e'),(1583,2479,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Admissions'),(1584,2479,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1585,2479,'sidebar','Admissions'),(1586,2479,'header','yes'),(1587,2479,'footer',''),(1588,2479,'_edit_lock','1552289118:11'),(1589,2480,'_edit_last','11'),(1590,2480,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1591,2480,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(27286,2480,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Application for Admission</h1>\r\nTo learn more about our admission application requirements, please visit our <a title=\"Admissions : Applying for Admission\" href=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/admissions-how-to-apply/\">Applying for Admission</a> page. For supplementary forms, such as Teacher Evaluation and Request for Transcripts, please visit our <a title=\"Admissions : Admission Forms\" href=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/admissions-applications/\">Admission Forms </a>page.<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n<h2>Preschool, Kindergarten or Grade School Application Form</h2>\r\n[contact-form-7 id=\"3989\" title=\"Admission Application Form\"]\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 105%;\">Please click the button below to pay the $75 application fee</span> using PayPal. It is not necessary to have a PayPal account. Please also review <a href=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/admissions-how-to-apply/#toggle-id-1\">application requirements.</a> Other required forms can be found <a href=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/admissions-applications/\">here.</a>\r\n\r\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\"><input name=\"cmd\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"_s-xclick\" />\r\n<input name=\"hosted_button_id\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"YN9YWUSK4RTPN\" />\r\n<input class=\"ppsprite\" alt=\"\" name=\"pay\" src=\"/learn/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/spacer.png\" type=\"image\" />\r\n<img src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" /></form>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -45px;\">Please send us a photo of your student applicant by <a href=\"mailto: admissions@threecedarswaldorf.org\">email</a>.</p>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n'),(1593,2480,'layout',''),(1594,2480,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','b24e14af4b'),(1595,2480,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Admissions'),(1596,2480,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1597,2480,'sidebar','Admissions'),(1598,2480,'header','yes'),(1599,2480,'footer',''),(1600,2480,'_edit_lock','1551683459:11'),(1601,2481,'_edit_last','14'),(1602,2481,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1603,2481,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active',''),(1604,2481,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData',''),(1605,2481,'layout',''),(1606,2481,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','1ed289021a'),(1607,2481,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Admissions'),(1608,2481,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1609,2481,'sidebar','Admissions'),(1610,2481,'header','yes'),(1611,2481,'footer',''),(1612,2481,'_edit_lock','1550227522:14'),(1613,2482,'_edit_last','11'),(1614,2482,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1615,2482,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(1616,2482,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Programs and Curriculum Overview</h1>\r\n<h2>Inspired to Learn, Prepared to Thrive</h2>\r\nAt Eastside Community School, we are inspired by the educational philosophies of Waldorf Education. Each school year is designed to meet children’s evolving aptitude for experiences and social interactions. Because our students cultivate unique intellectual, emotional, physical, and spiritual capacities while developing their academic skills, they emerge with the freedom to act and think, confident in themselves, their path, and their place in the world.\r\n<h2>About Waldorf Education</h2>\r\nWaldorf<sup>®</sup> Education is rooted in a profound understanding of how children learn and grow, based on the principles of education from world-renowned, scientist, artist, and founder of Anthroposophy Rudolf Steiner. This approach nurtures the natural joy that children take in learning with lessons not simply based on repetition and memorization, but imbued with arts and experienced through immersive, hands-on participation.\r\n<h2>Open Houses and Tours</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888admissions-open-houses-tours/\">View our current Open House and Tour schedule.</a>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_hr class=\'default\' height=\'50\' shadow=\'no-shadow\' position=\'center\' custom_border=\'av-border-thin\' custom_width=\'50px\' custom_border_color=\'\' custom_margin_top=\'30px\' custom_margin_bottom=\'30px\' icon_select=\'yes\' custom_icon_color=\'\' icon=\'ue808\']\r\n\r\n[av_blog blog_type=\'posts\' categories=\'85\' link=\'category\' blog_style=\'blog-grid\' columns=\'3\' contents=\'excerpt\' content_length=\'content\' preview_mode=\'auto\' image_size=\'portfolio\' items=\'3\' offset=\'0\' paginate=\'yes\' conditional=\'\']\r\n\r\n'),(1617,2482,'layout',''),(1618,2482,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','565a5cd8ef'),(1619,2482,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Programs and Curriculum'),(1620,2482,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1621,2482,'sidebar','Programs and Curriculum'),(1622,2482,'header','yes'),(1623,2482,'footer',''),(1624,2482,'_edit_lock','1552285449:11'),(1625,2483,'_edit_last','11'),(1626,2483,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1627,2483,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(1628,2483,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Early Childhood Program</h1>\r\n<h2>Enjoying Play with a Purpose</h2>\r\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">In our early childhood classrooms, great care is taken to create a warm and home-like setting and a beautiful environment where children\'s senses are nurtured. Every aspect of our early childhood program is designed to foster healthy and balanced intellectual, emotional, and physical development from daily outdoor play and nature walks to the organic foods served at snack time. Our students learn by engaging in practical activities such as washing dishes, sweeping, gardening, baking and building. We incorporate seasonal crafts, movement, outdoor adventures, and ample creative free play to encourage joyful learning and imaginative exploration.</span>\r\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">\r\nEastside Community School offers preschool and kindergarten for three- to six-year old children (children must turn three by September 1). We request that your child be fully potty-trained, able to eat on his or her own, and cooperative in dressing for outdoor play.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> Our early childhood program focuses on:</span>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_toggle_container initial=\'0\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Imagination\' tags=\'\']\r\nYoung children are supported in their natural development by an emphasis on imagination as explored through play, purposeful activity, movement, social life, art and a rich tradition of oral storytelling, all provided in a warm and secure environment.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Simple Play\' tags=\'\']\r\nThe kind of playful work in which children engage in the our school is very different from the media-saturated expectations generated by most modern toys and electronic games. We provide young children many opportunities for undirected play while guiding them in creating a healthy social group with their peers.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Rhythm\' tags=\'\']\r\n<o>Because a consistent, dependable daily rhythm provides a critical sense of security for a young child, activities are scheduled to follow the natural rhythms of a child’s day and year, balancing indoor and outdoor free play with more focused artistic and practical activities such as baking, painting, or crafts, and with circle time including rhymes, songs, and storytelling.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Beauty\' tags=\'\']\r\nOur classrooms are designed to support the child’s foundational experience that the world is good and beautiful.  Classrooms are pleasant with calm areas for working and playing, our toys and art supplies are created from natural materials, and our outdoor areas include playgrounds, grassy fields, and natural woods for magical adventures.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Purposeful Activity\' tags=\'\']\r\nYoung children begin school enthusiastic and excited to learn. Our activities prepare them for the challenges of elementary school subjects while nurturing and maintaining their enthusiasm:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Songs, stories and rhymes cultivate intimacy with language</li>\r\n	<li>Puppet shows and dramatic play strengthen memory and imagination</li>\r\n	<li>Counting games and rhythmic activities build a solid foundation for arithmetic skills</li>\r\n	<li>Painting and crafts help develop fine motor skills, coordination, and concentration</li>\r\n	<li>Vigorous play enhances concentration as it develops gross motor skills, proprioception, and vitality</li>\r\n	<li>Seasonal and outdoor activities foster understanding of the natural world</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h2>Open Houses and Tours</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888admissions-open-houses-tours/\">View our current Open House and Tour schedule.</a>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n'),(1629,2483,'layout',''),(1630,2483,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','e8d3b3e07e'),(1631,2483,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Programs and Curriculum : Early Childhood'),(1632,2483,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1633,2483,'sidebar','Programs and Curriculum : Early Childhood'),(1634,2483,'header','yes'),(1635,2483,'footer',''),(1636,2483,'_edit_lock','1552284815:11'),(1637,2484,'_edit_last','11'),(1638,2484,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1639,2484,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(10857,2484,'_avia_builder_shortcode_tree','a:2:{i:0;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:12:\"av_textblock\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:0;}i:1;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:19:\"av_toggle_container\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:1;}}'),(10225,5507,'_wp_attached_file','2013/12/Parent-Tot_Registration.pdf'),(1641,2484,'layout',''),(1642,2484,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','6b4797a413'),(1643,2484,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Programs and Curriculum : Early Childhood'),(1644,2484,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1645,2484,'sidebar','Programs and Curriculum : Early Childhood'),(1646,2484,'header','yes'),(1647,2484,'footer',''),(1648,2484,'_edit_lock','1552284855:11'),(1649,2485,'_edit_last','11'),(1650,2485,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1651,2485,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(1652,2485,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Preschool</h1>\r\n<h2>Reveling in Childhood</h2>\r\nWe help children ages three to four happily and successfully transition from home life to school life with our innovative preschool approach. Following a daily rhythm well-suited to their natural development, our preschool helps young students begin to expand their social circle, enrich their imaginations, and expand their physical activities in a peaceful, nurturing environment.\r\n<h2>Exploring Their Expanding World</h2>\r\nPreschool at Eastside Community School is about reveling in both childhood and the world, with children spending ample time in and out of doors. Outside, they explore nature as they splash in puddles, marvel at budding daffodils, or run with the winds. Inside, they learn to play together, use toys made from natural materials, and enjoy homemade snacks to stay fueled for movement and fun.\r\n\r\nActivities also mark the rhythm of the changing natural world throughout the year. In the fall, children might cut and cook apples for applesauce and make lanterns to lighten the growing darkness. In the spring, they might help prepare a snack using organic vegetables.\r\n\r\nRegular parent evenings are held throughout the school year for parents to ask questions and share resources, and where we also explore the foundations of an early childhood experience inspired by Waldorf education. Private annual conferences offer parents time to discuss their child’s development in-depth with the teacher.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_toggle_container initial=\'1\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Details\' tags=\'\']\r\n<strong>Class Sessions:</strong> Three-day (M, T, W) and five-day options available, with choice of morning program or extended day\r\n\r\n<strong>School Hours:</strong> Morning program is 8:00 a.m. to 12:00 p.m.; Extended day is 8:00 a.m. to 2:45 p.m.\r\n<strong>Ages:</strong> Three to four years old; children must be three by September 1 and potty trained\r\n<strong>Class Size:</strong> Up to 8 children, 2 teachers\r\n<strong>Food Provided: </strong>Yes\r\n<strong>After-School Care:</strong> Available from dismissal time until 6:00 p.m.\r\n\r\n<em>Note: After-school care is available for extended day students. There is no after-school care for morning program students.</em>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Open Houses, Tours and Admission Information\' tags=\'\']\r\n<!--To learn more about our preschool program, please join us for an <a title=\"Admissions : Open Houses & Tours\" href=\"/admissions-open-houses-tours/\">open house or school tour,</a> and visit the <a title=\"Admissions : Applying for Admission\" href=\"/admissions-how-to-apply/\">Admissions</a> section of our website for information on how to apply, tuition, and application forms.-->\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888admissions-open-houses-tours/\">View our current Open House and Tour schedule.</a>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]\r\n\r\n'),(1653,2485,'layout',''),(1654,2485,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','5e0e3c5bbf'),(1655,2485,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Programs and Curriculum : Early Childhood'),(1656,2485,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1657,2485,'sidebar','Programs and Curriculum : Early Childhood'),(1658,2485,'header','yes'),(1659,2485,'footer',''),(1660,2485,'_edit_lock','1552285504:11'),(1661,2486,'_edit_last','11'),(1662,2486,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1663,2486,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(1664,2486,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Kindergarten</h1>\r\n<h2>Nurturing the Treasure of Imagination</h2>\r\nThe kindergarten experience at Eastside Community School is devoted to nurturing the most precious aspect of early childhood: imagination. In a mixed-age classroom, children sing songs, learn poems, perform puppet plays, and take part in circle games—all helping attune them to the beauty of language as their imaginations flourish.\r\n\r\nThey begin to awaken their sense of taste, sight, beauty and purpose through activities like baking bread, drawing, and painting. We carefully select classroom toys and tools made from natural materials such as wood, silk, or beeswax, materials that appeal to the sense of touch and help foster a reverence for nature. Children enjoy both movement and nature during outside play, walks, and gardening.\r\n\r\nBecause our kindergarten includes a mix of preschool and kindergarten age children, and regular weekly interaction with children in our preschool, our kindergarten students enjoy participating in a variety of social groups and rites of passage. When they act as helpers and role models for the younger children, they nurture qualities that will serve them well throughout life.\r\n\r\nRegular parent evenings are held throughout the school year for parents to ask questions and share resources, and where we also explore the foundations of an early childhood experience inspired by Waldorf education. Private annual conferences offer parents time to discuss their child’s development in-depth with the teacher.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_toggle_container initial=\'1\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Details\' tags=\'\']\r\n<strong>Class Sessions:</strong> Five day program, with choice of morning program or extended day\r\n\r\n<strong>School Hours:</strong> Morning program 8:00 a.m. to 12:00 p.m.; Extended day 8:00 a.m. to 2:45 p.m.\r\n<strong>Ages:</strong> For children four to six. Children as young as three may be accepted in the Kindergarten class, pending teachers’ assessment.\r\n<strong>Class Size:</strong> Up to 20 children, 2 teachers\r\n<strong>Food Provided:</strong> Yes\r\n<strong>After-School Care:</strong> Available from dismissal time until 6:00 p.m.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Open Houses, Tours and Admission Information\' tags=\'\']\r\n<!--To learn more about our kindergarten program, please join us for an <a title=\"Admissions : Open Houses & Tours\" href=\"/admissions-open-houses-tours/\">open house or school tour,</a> and visit the <a title=\"Admissions : Applying for Admission\" href=\"/admissions-how-to-apply/\">Admissions</a> section of our website for information on how to apply, tuition and application forms.-->\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888admissions-open-houses-tours/\">View our current Open House and Tour schedule.</a>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]\r\n\r\n'),(1665,2486,'layout',''),(1666,2486,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','b25ded626a'),(1667,2486,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Programs and Curriculum : Early Childhood'),(1668,2486,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1669,2486,'sidebar','Programs and Curriculum : Early Childhood'),(1670,2486,'header','yes'),(1671,2486,'footer',''),(1672,2486,'_edit_lock','1552285410:11'),(1673,2487,'_edit_last','8'),(1674,2487,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1675,2487,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(1676,2487,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Early Childhood Curriculum Overview</h1>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_table purpose=\'tabular\' pricing_table_design=\'avia_pricing_default\' pricing_hidden_cells=\'\' caption=\'\' responsive_styling=\'avia_scrollable_table\']\r\n[av_row row_style=\'avia-heading-row\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\'][/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Parent & Tot Class[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Preschool [/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Kindergarten[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\']<strong>Daily \r\nRhythm</strong>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>Arrival</li>\r\n	<li>Indoor play</li>\r\n	<li>Inside circle with songs, finger games, movement,  and verse</li>\r\n	<li>Snack preparation and sharing</li>\r\n	<li>Outdoor play in yard</li>\r\n	<li>Good-bye</li>\r\n</ul>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>Arrival and daily activity</li>\r\n	<li>Indoor play</li>\r\n	<li>Circle – story, songs and finger games</li>\r\n	<li>Snack</li>\r\n	<li>Walk</li>\r\n	<li>Outdoor play</li>\r\n	<li>Story</li>\r\n	<li>Departure for morning students</li>\r\n	<li>Lunch and rest/nap for extended day students</li>\r\n</ul>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>Arrival and daily activity</li>\r\n	<li>Indoor play</li>\r\n	<li>Circle – story, songs and finger games</li>\r\n	<li>Snack</li>\r\n	<li>Walk</li>\r\n	<li>Outdoor play</li>\r\n	<li>Story</li>\r\n	<li>Departure for morning students</li>\r\n	<li>Lunch and rest/nap for extended day students</li>\r\n</ul>[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\']<strong>Weekly Activities</strong>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Not applicable[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>Watercolor painting</li>\r\n	<li>Grain grinding</li>\r\n	<li>Bread baking</li>\r\n	<li>Woodworking</li>\r\n	<li>Cleaning</li>\r\n</ul>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>Vegetable chopping</li>\r\n	<li>Watercolor painting</li>\r\n	<li>Drawing</li>\r\n	<li>Sewing</li>\r\n	<li>Finger knitting</li>\r\n	<li>Grain grinding</li>\r\n	<li>Bread baking</li>\r\n	<li>Woodworking</li>\r\n	<li>Gardening</li>\r\n	<li>Cleaning</li>\r\n</ul>[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\']<strong>Seasonal Rhythm</strong>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Craft and circle activities are chosen to reflect the season[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Crafts and circle activities, chosen to reflect the season, along with seasonal celebrations: Michaelmas, Lantern Walk, and Spring Parade[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Crafts and circle activities, chosen to reflect the season, along with seasonal celebrations: Michaelmas, Lantern Walk, and Spring Parade[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\']<strong>Age Range</strong>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']12 – 36 months\r\nWith one parent or caregiver\r\n(3 or younger by September 1)[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']For children ages 3 – 4 years old\r\nMust be 3 by September 1[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Ages 3½ – 6 years old\r\nMust be 3½ by September 1\r\nMixed-age program[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\']<strong>Schedule</strong>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']One class per week\r\n9:30 a.m. – 11:30 a.m.\r\nChoice of Wednesdays or Thursdays[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>3-day program: M, T, W</li>\r\n	<li>Choice of morning or extended day</li>\r\n	<li>Morning Program: 8:00 a.m. – 12:00 p.m.</li>\r\n	<li>Extended Day: 8:00 a.m. – 2:45 p.m.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>5-day program M – F</li>\r\n	<li>Choice of morning or extended day</li>\r\n	<li>Morning Program: 8:00 a.m. – 12:00 p.m.</li>\r\n	<li>Extended Day: 8:00 a.m. – 2:45 p.m.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\']<strong>After-School Care</strong>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Not available[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']From dismissal time until 6:00 p.m., for extended day students only; includes indoor and outdoor free play and a snack[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']From dismissal time until 6:00 p.m., for extended day students only; includes indoor and outdoor free play and a snack[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\']<strong>Tuition 2018-2019</strong>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Tuition information will be published soon. <!--Please visit our <a href=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/admissions-tuition/\">tuition page</a>-->[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Tuition information will be published soon. <!--Please visit our <a href=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/admissions-tuition/\">tuition page</a>-->[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Tuition information will be published soon. <!--Please visit our <a href=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/admissions-tuition/\">tuition page</a>-->[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[/av_table]\r\n\r\n'),(37556,8768,'_wp_attached_file','2016/05/Newsletter-Three-Cedars-Waldorf-School-2016-04-25.pdf'),(24593,6985,'_edit_last','2'),(24594,6985,'_wp_page_template','default'),(24595,6985,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(24596,6985,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock ]\r\n<h1>Admission Forms</h1>\r\nTo learn more about our admission application requirements, please visit our <a title=\"Admissions : Applying for Admission\" href=\"/admissions-how-to-apply/\">Applying for Admission</a> page.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Parent-Tot Registration</h2>\r\nPlease use the <a href=\"/learn/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/TCWS_ParentTot_RegForm_2014-15.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Parent-Tot Registration Form</a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Preschool and Kindergarten Admission Forms</h2>\r\n<a title=\"Admissions : Online Admission Application Form\" href=\"/admission-application-form/\">Online Admission Application Form</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/learn/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Kinder-PreK-Teacher-Eval-Fillable-Form.pdf \" target=\"_blank\">Teacher Evaluation Form for Preschool & Kindergarten Applicants</a>\r\nTo be completed by your child\'s current teacher or childcare provider\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Grade School Admission Forms</h2>\r\n<a title=\"Admissions : Online Admission Application Form\" href=\"/admission-application-form/\">Online Admission Application Form</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/learn/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Grades-Teacher-Evaluation-Fillable-Form.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Teacher Evaluation Form for Elementary Grades Applicants</a>\r\nTo be completed by your child\'s current teacher\r\n\r\n<a href=\"/learn/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Request-Transcripts-Fill-In-AdobeReader.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Request for Transcripts</a>\r\nSend the completed form to your child\'s current school (applicants to grades 2-8 only)\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://get.adobe.com/reader/\" target=\"_blank\">Get Adobe Reader</a>\r\nTo use fill-able PDF forms, please save the form on your computer, and open in Adobe Reader.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n'),(1677,2487,'layout',''),(1678,2487,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','ba1b153bab'),(1679,2487,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Programs and Curriculum : Early Childhood'),(1680,2487,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1681,2487,'sidebar','Programs and Curriculum : Early Childhood'),(1682,2487,'header','yes'),(1683,2487,'footer',''),(1684,2487,'_edit_lock','1552285145:11'),(1685,2488,'_edit_last','11'),(1686,2488,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1687,2488,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(1688,2488,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Grade School and Middle School</h1>\r\n<h2>A Strong Sense of Academics and of Self</h2>\r\nThe key to education at Eastside Community School is balance: between students’ practical knowledge and their creative enthusiasm; in a rich curriculum where challenging academics are integrated with arts, music, and movement; and where we ensure that learning happens naturally and rhythmically while helping develop students’ skill and interest in a variety of subjects and activities.\r\n\r\n<!--Each day begins with a two-hour main lesson of reading, writing, math, history, geography or science, taught in blocks of three to four weeks.--> Subjects are made engaging and exciting by teachers skilled in oral storytelling and by integrating each subject with a variety of arts. This overview represents the current planned curriculum for Eastside Community School. As our programs are defined, this page will be updated.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_toggle_container initial=\'0\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Grade School\' tags=\'\']\r\nStudents don’t merely absorb the subjects taught in the two-hour main lesson. Instead, they reach a deep understanding of each lesson by bringing it to life in books that they design, write, and illustrate about each subject.\r\n\r\nDay-to-day learning takes place in a non-competitive environment. Parents receive regular updates through parent-teacher conferences, written evaluations of student progress, thanks to close relationships between teachers, students, and families. Teachers and students often progress together from first grade through the middle school years.\r\n\r\nOther teachers add to the weekly rhythm by sharing their specialties in language instruction, music, handwork, and movement education.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Middle School\' tags=\'\']\r\nMiddle school students are anxious to explore their world, so we strike a balance between a comforting continuity from the lower grades and increased academic and artistic challenges.\r\n\r\nStudents participate in multi-day trips such as biking, hiking and kayaking, bringing hands-on experiences linked to the academic curriculum. In eighth grade, all students complete a comprehensive research project, complete with written report, artistic project, display, and oral presentation to the school community.\r\n\r\nThis comprehensive approach to academics, the arts, and hands-on activities prepares students well for the challenges of high school. And they take with them a healthy, inclusive approach to social relationships, as they refine their ability to work as a team and to respect each other\'s individuality.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Details\' tags=\'\']\r\nThe grade school day begins at 8:00 a.m. and ends at 3:00 p.m. <a href=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/curriculum-programs-after-school-care/\">After-School Care</a> is available as well.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h2>Open Houses and Tours</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888admissions-open-houses-tours/\">View our current Open House and Tour schedule.</a>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n'),(24401,5615,'_thumbnail_id','3102'),(1689,2488,'layout',''),(1690,2488,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','d658a35737'),(1691,2488,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Programs and Curriculum : Grades'),(1692,2488,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1693,2488,'sidebar','Programs and Curriculum : Grades'),(1694,2488,'header','yes'),(1695,2488,'footer',''),(1696,2488,'_edit_lock','1552285116:11'),(1697,2489,'_edit_last','11'),(1698,2489,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1699,2489,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(1700,2489,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Academics</h1>\r\n<h2>An Education Not Simply Accomplished, But Lived</h2>\r\n<!--Eastside Community School is currently working to renew our affiliation with the Association of Waldorf Schools of North America. A Waldorf<sup>®</sup> Education is designed to impart knowledge in a meaningful way.--> We are basing our curriculum on a profound understanding of human development, with the insight that comprehensive and rigorous academics should be exciting, engaging, and imbued with artistic expression.\r\n\r\nEastside Community School intends to provide a rich variety of subjects and activities for grade school students, all taught in harmony with the different stages of child development. Our students will emerge with knowledge, courage, enthusiasm, creativity and a solid sense of how to reason. They will meet the world ready to face life’s challenges.\r\n\r\n<strong>Planned Curriculum: </strong>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_toggle_container initial=\'1\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Science\' tags=\'\']\r\nOur approach to science is similar to the process of discovery that scientists have undertaken for ages: exploring the natural processes around us, demonstrating phenomena, and asking students to explain the cause through observation and by drawing conclusions.\r\n\r\nYounger children learn the basics of science through outdoor play and experimentation in nature. In grades three through five, plant and animal facts are connected to human activities through storytelling. Formal lab science begins in grade six.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Math\' tags=\'\']\r\nWe take math from the written page into the physical world, teaching young students mathematical basics in part through movement of the body. Students might clap the multiplication tables, find Pythagoras’ theorem with lentils, or walk the addition of negative and positive numbers. Not only do activities strengthen number sense and confident computation, they enhance students’ performance during daily, more traditional mental and written math exercises. The combined approach helps prepare students for challenges such as algebra, geometry and business math in middle school.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Language Arts\' tags=\'\']\r\nStorytelling is at the heart of learning to understand and to love the English language. Students compose stories based on their learning and read what they wrote to others—both exciting steps as they progress toward the complex expression of moods in poetry and short story plots. The study of grammar as the skeleton of language supports this writing as well as the scientific summaries and works students create for other subjects. Drama and oral recitation deepen the students’ speaking and acting skills as well as their understanding of myths and classics.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Geography\' tags=\'\']\r\nOur geography curriculum begins in our own schoolyard and expands through the years to cover people and places worldwide. The depth and breadth of understanding develops as the students do, with map-making beginning in grade four and gaining complexity as they progress.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'World Mythology and History\' tags=\'\']\r\n<!--Just as a Waldorf Education follows the pattern of a child’s developmental stages,-->Our curriculum follows the pattern that has unfolded throughout human history. We explore the development of civilization and the great stories of all time, from fairy tales and fables to Nordic and Greek myths to medieval, Roman, Renaissance, and modern history, which the class teacher brings to life through oral storytelling. Written and artistic work follows, further deepening students’ understanding.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h2>Open Houses and Tours</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888admissions-open-houses-tours/\">View our current Open House and Tour schedule.</a>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n'),(1701,2489,'layout',''),(1702,2489,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','dc36964113'),(1703,2489,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Programs and Curriculum : Grades'),(1704,2489,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1705,2489,'sidebar','Programs and Curriculum : Grades'),(1706,2489,'header','yes'),(1707,2489,'footer',''),(1708,2489,'_edit_lock','1552285507:11'),(1709,2490,'_edit_last','11'),(1710,2490,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1711,2490,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(1712,2490,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h2>Arts Integration</h2>\r\nAt Eastside Community School, the arts are not “extras,” but an integral part of the everyday curriculum—both as individual arts classes and as part of the main lesson. For example, first grade students draw pictures of the stories they hear, which evolve into the forms of the letters they study. By the seventh grade, students learn to draw with perspective, tying into their study of Renaissance art as well as geometry. Painting and modeling complement math study, develop dexterity and mastery of hand-tools, and engage the students in an experience of practical competency.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_toggle_container initial=\'0\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Visual Arts\' tags=\'\']\r\nBecause our curriculum is enlivened with the arts, students at Eastside Community School work on their fine art skills on a daily and weekly basis. Painting in watercolors, acrylics, and oils, black and white and color drawing in pencil and pastel, woodworking, beeswax and clay sculpture are all introduced at a time most appropriate to the stages of child development.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Performing Arts\' tags=\'\']\r\nWhen students sing, act and play instruments, they develop a deep appreciation of the arts and of their own talents and also gain confidence in public speaking and performance. Each year, every grade school student takes part in a play, with increasingly complex involvement in the play production and performance as they grow older.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Music\' tags=\'\']\r\nIn grades one through eight, students learn to sing and play recorders together, in unison, rounds, canons and multiple parts, led by the class teacher as part of the daily activities, and in support of the main lesson curriculum.\r\n\r\nIn grade four, each student begins to play a string instrument in a twice-weekly orchestra class with our specialty strings teachers. Music reading begins, and daily home practice is expected. In grade six, students may choose ukulele class as an alternate.\r\n\r\nChoir begins in grade six with an emphasis on developing the voice in a healthy manner, using various vocal colors and techniques, and introducing a wide variety of musical styles.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Handwork\' tags=\'\']\r\nEvery student takes part in handwork class to not only create work that is meaningful and beautiful, but because the rhythmic, purposeful movement of hands as they knit, crochet, cross-stitch, embroider, felt, and sew is a blueprint for the process of receiving, integrating, and using abstract concepts of higher learning.\r\n\r\nHandwork provides rich “felt experiences” through touch, smell, and movement, which also activate neural pathways in the brain. There is simply a deeper connection made when a child who is learning about wool experiences petting a sheep, washing and carding its wool, and then using that wool to felt, knit, or crochet.\r\n\r\nIn the first three years of grade school, children learn to knit and crochet—the beginning of their deeper connection with the natural world and of orderly, joyful work habits. In fourth grade, students focus on cross-stitch. In fifth grade, embroidery and knitting. In middle school, patterns are introduced as students piece together projects for felting and sewing.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h2>Open Houses and Tours</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888admissions-open-houses-tours/\">View our current Open House and Tour schedule.</a>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n'),(1713,2490,'layout',''),(1714,2490,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','94593644fb'),(1715,2490,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Programs and Curriculum : Grades'),(1716,2490,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1717,2490,'sidebar','Programs and Curriculum : Grades'),(1718,2490,'header','yes'),(1719,2490,'footer',''),(1720,2490,'_edit_lock','1552285336:11'),(1721,2491,'_edit_last','11'),(1722,2491,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1723,2491,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active',''),(1724,2491,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData',''),(1725,2491,'layout',''),(1726,2491,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','081cfd429f'),(1727,2491,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Programs and Curriculum : Grades'),(1728,2491,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1729,2491,'sidebar','Programs and Curriculum : Grades'),(1730,2491,'header','yes'),(1731,2491,'footer',''),(1732,2491,'_edit_lock','1552285267:11'),(1733,2492,'_edit_last','11'),(1734,2492,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1735,2492,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active',''),(1736,2492,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock ]\r\n<h1>Movement Education</h1>\r\n<h2>Eurythmy</h2>\r\nThroughout their education at Three Cedars, children take part in Eurythmy, a unique art developed by Rudolf Steiner with his wife, Marie von Sivers, where speech and music are interpreted through movement.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_toggle_container initial=\'0\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Early Grades\' tags=\'\']\r\nIn the early grades, we channel children’s natural play into formed movement, where they learn to use and trust the movement of their own bodies by imitating Eurythmy instructors. Later, we guide them toward more exact movements in rhythm with the spoken word. The movement and quality of speech is explored through letters, then carried further via poetry and verse.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Higher Grades\' tags=\'\']\r\nIn the higher grades, students learn to move in different directions, form moving geometrical shapes, and to shape their movements based on musical tones and the sounds of the words in poetry. Group formations teach them to harmonize their own movements with those of a group. Exercises using copper rods help the body and mind cooperate and build strength and accuracy.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock ]\r\n<h2>Physical Education</h2>\r\nGames and movement are critical to shaping growth: physical, social, and emotional. That’s why physical education at Three Cedars Waldorf School is not focused only on the benefits of exercise, but is a complete program of balanced spatial education.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_toggle_container initial=\'0\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Early Grades\' tags=\'\']\r\nIn the lower grades, physical education ties into the overall focus on imagination; we strengthen the child’s spatial awareness with creative games that include string and clapping games, body geography, and bean bags, as well as circle and tag games. By the fourth grade, we satisfy children’s awakening intellects with games that achieve a task or solve a problem.\r\n\r\nFifth-grade students practice for the regional Olympiad, a sports event that emphasizes grace, beauty and skill in the tradition of the ancient Greeks, to complement their academic study of ancient civilizations. Bothmer movement exercises are also introduced to support the students’ developing spatial awareness.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Higher Grades\' tags=\'\']\r\nIn middle school, students learn to position and conduct themselves in a team during games that use a sense of formation, while circus skills and gymnastics demand all-around skill, spatial awareness, and courage. A seventh and eighth grade regional track meet provides another opportunity for the students to challenge themselves as well as to meet students from other Waldorf schools.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]\r\n\r\n'),(1737,2492,'layout',''),(1738,2492,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','7df980d178'),(1739,2492,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Programs and Curriculum : Grades'),(1740,2492,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1741,2492,'sidebar','Programs and Curriculum : Grades'),(1742,2492,'header','yes'),(1743,2492,'footer',''),(1744,2492,'_edit_lock','1552285236:11'),(1745,2493,'_edit_last','14'),(1746,2493,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1747,2493,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(1748,2493,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Grade School Curriculum Overview</h1>\r\n<a id=\"one\" name=\"one\"></a>\r\n<h2>This overview represents the current planned curriculum for Eastside Community School. As our programs are defined, this page will be updated.</h2>\r\n<h2>Grades 1 – 4</h2>\r\n<strong><a title=\"Programs and Curriculum : Grade School : Curriculum Overview Chart\" href=\"/curriculum-programs-grade-school-curriculum-overview-chart/#five\">Jump down</a> </strong>to view curriculum for grades 5 – 8.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_table purpose=\'tabular\' caption=\'\']\r\n[av_row row_style=\'avia-heading-row\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\'][/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Grade One[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Grade Two[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Grade Three[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Grade Four[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\