(1811,2498,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','About Us'),(1812,2498,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1813,2498,'sidebar','About Us'),(1814,2498,'header','yes'),(1815,2498,'footer',''),(1816,2498,'_edit_lock','1542582504:11'),(1817,2499,'_edit_last','2'),(1818,2499,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1819,2499,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(1820,2499,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Staff</h1>\r\nIn January 2016, Three Cedars Waldorf School merged with Seattle Waldorf School. Three Cedars staff bios are listed below. To learn more about our colleagues at Seattle Waldorf School, please click <a href=\"http://www.seattlewaldorf.org/our-school/faculty-staff/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.\r\n<h2><img class=\"size-full wp-image-3732 alignleft\" src=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/learn/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/FS_Campana_Annette_Teacher_2015_crp.jpg\" alt=\"FS_Campana_Annette_Teacher_2015_crp\" width=\"96\" height=\"120\" />Annette Campana, Pedagogical Chair</h2>\r\nAnnette Campana was born and raised in Vancouver, British Columbia. She attended the Cleveland Institute of Music before returning to BC, where she earned her Bachelor of Education Degree from Simon Fraser University. Ms. Campana taught public middle school, first in British Columbia and later in New Jersey. After the arrival of her two daughters, she discovered Waldorf Education, and was deeply inspired as an educator by the insightful and developmentally thoughtful educational approach. Ms. Campana completed her Waldorf teacher training at Antioch University New England, and then worked at the Waldorf School of Princeton as a grade school teacher, early childhood teacher, and choir director. Upon returning to the West Coast, she was excited to again carry a class through their middle school years and graduate the 2015 class at Three Cedars. She enjoys music, a cup a tea, a good book, but most of all spending time with her family in the wonderful outdoors.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-7350\" src=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/learn/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/FS_Jeantette_Tabatha_Assistant_AppleBlossom_crp.jpg\" alt=\"FS_Jones_Laurin\" width=\"96\" height=\"120\" /></h1>\r\n<h2>Tabatha Jeantette, Admissions and Development Coordinator</h2>\r\nTabatha Jeantette is the oldest of four brothers and one sister born and raised in Northern New Mexico. She attended college at Albuquerque Technical Vocational Institute, where she earned her degree in Business Administration. During her college years, she was selected from the Department of Energy in Washington, D.C. to be part of a classified workstation at Sandia National Laboratories. She has also worked for an International Commercial Real Estate Company in its Education and Training Department and in the Marketing and Global Events Department. Miss Tabatha became extensively involved in Waldorf Education upon the births of her three daughters; she has been learning about, working in, and striving to improve her knowledge and understanding of Waldorf Education ever since. Her love for the Pacific Northwest prompted a move back to Seattle in 2006. Since that time, she has been part of the Three Cedars Community as an active Parent Volunteer, Class Coordinator, After-School Care Teacher, Substitute Teacher, Kindergarten Assistant, and Admissions and Development Coordinator.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-3749\" src=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/learn/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/FS_Collier_Pam-OfficeManager_crp.jpg\" alt=\"FS_Collier_Pam-OfficeManager_crp\" width=\"96\" height=\"120\" /></h2>\r\n<h2>Pamela Collier, Information Systems Manager</h2>\r\nPamela was born in Wisconsin and has fond memories of wandering through the woods and along the shores of Lake Michigan. At age nine, she moved to California with her family and grew to love sunshine, mountains, Pacific beaches, avocados, and the piano. She earned her BA in English from California Polytechnic State University in San Luis Obispo and made a career of technical writing, editing, and content management, mostly for software technology companies. Pamela has lived in the Seattle area since 1995, where her son and daughter joyfully attend Three Cedars Waldorf School. She is on a quest to organize and optimize the necessary business and details of life to make room for many interests that include walking, hiking, paddle boarding, yoga, inquiry, meditation, nutrition, piano, and knitting.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-8484\" src=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/learn/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/TCWS_staff_NeyssaLeePhotography-0707-e1454604175901-251x300.jpg\" alt=\"Shelly McSweyn, Registrar  Bookkeeper\" width=\"92\" height=\"110\" />Shelly McSweyn, Registrar and Bookkeeper</h2>\r\n\"Miss Shelly\" joined the Three Cedars staff in 2015, bringing rich administrative experience from being a business owner of 29 years, receptionist for Seattle Waldorf School, and receptionist and bookkeeper for an anthroposophical doctor. Her daughter is a graduate of Seattle Waldorf High School. Shelly is an avid knitter and cook and loves to walk.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-3749\" src=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/learn/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/FS_Snyder_Geri_AdminAssistant_crp.jpg\" alt=\"FS_Snyder_Geri_AdminAssistant_crp\" width=\"96\" height=\"120\" /></h2>\r\n<h2>Geri Snyder, After-School Care Manager</h2>\r\nGeri Snyder\'s early life was spent on a wonderful farm in western Kansas where she learned to love nature through vegetable gardening, helping with the maize crop, and seeing the sparrows, cotton-tailed bunnies, turtles, and coyotes, along with the farm animals. All things spiritual were precious to her, which grew into reverence for many cultures experienced throughout her life, and opened up an interest in different healing modalities, from using herbs to faith healing. Fairy tales and books opened even more realms of delight, as did outdoor activities such as tennis, skiing, hiking, boating, camping, and flying with her father in single-engine planes. Experiencing university and college life expanded her horizons in learning with a special love for literature, anthropology, and religious philosophies. Making gifts and celebrating festivals and special events were highlights in her life that led to her becoming a Waldorf kindergarten teacher for 18 years in California, Colorado, and Washington. Even the difficult times in her life brought the wisdom to step above them and seek the positive. Geri enjoys supporting the faculty, students and families at Three Cedars Waldorf School as an Administrative Assistant and looks forward to loving the gift of life each day.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-3749\" src=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/learn/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/FS_Pressey_Chris.jpg\" alt=\"Pressey_Chris.jpg\" width=\"96\" height=\"120\" />Chris Pressey, Facilities Manager</h2>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Chris grew up in a small town in Ohio and attended the University of Cincinnati where he received a Bachelor\'s degree in Civil Engineering.  A two-week Baker, Adams and Rainier climbing course brought Chris to the Northwest and started a life-long love of hiking and climbing.  This also precipitated relocation to Seattle following a 12-month road trip where he attempted to climb the highest peak in all 50 states.  </span><br style=\"color: #000000;\" /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Chris comes to us with a wealth of hands-on maintenance and repair skills from building, owning and operating rental houses. In addition to his formal education and work experience as a consulting engineer, Chris is a Licensed Professional Engineer (PE), a Certified Facilities Manager (CFM) and an Accredited Professional in Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design with a special designation in Building Design and Construction (LEED BD+C).  </span>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_hr class=\'default\' height=\'50\' shadow=\'no-shadow\' position=\'center\']\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\nTo email a staff member, please use their first initial and entire last name, followed by @threecedarswaldorf.org, or use our <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/contact-us/\">contact form</a> and our office will forward your message.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n'),(27399,7481,'_edit_lock','1430775487:4'),(27400,7481,'_edit_last','4'),(27401,7481,'_EventShowMapLink',''),(27402,7481,'_EventShowMap',''),(27403,7481,'_EventAllDay','yes'),(27404,7481,'_EventStartDate','2015-05-19 00:00:00'),(27405,7481,'_EventEndDate','2015-05-20 23:59:59'),(27406,7481,'_EventDuration','172799'),(27407,7481,'_EventVenueID','3041'),(27408,7481,'_EventCurrencySymbol','$'),(27409,7481,'_EventCurrencyPosition','prefix'),(27410,7481,'_EventCost',''),(27411,7481,'_EventURL',''),(27412,7481,'_EventOrganizerID','3400'),(27413,7481,'_EventRecurrence','a:15:{s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"None\";s:8:\"end-type\";s:2:\"On\";s:3:\"end\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"end-count\";s:1:\"1\";s:11:\"custom-type\";s:5:\"Daily\";s:15:\"custom-interval\";s:0:\"\";s:16:\"custom-type-text\";s:0:\"\";s:21:\"occurrence-count-text\";s:0:\"\";s:19:\"custom-month-number\";s:5:\"First\";s:16:\"custom-month-day\";s:1:\"1\";s:24:\"custom-year-month-number\";s:1:\"1\";s:21:\"custom-year-month-day\";s:1:\"1\";s:22:\"recurrence-description\";s:0:\"\";s:14:\"EventStartDate\";s:19:\"2015-05-19 00:00:00\";s:12:\"EventEndDate\";s:19:\"2015-05-20 23:59:59\";}'),(1821,2499,'layout',''),(1822,2499,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','4e220c5e20'),(1823,2499,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','About Us'),(1824,2499,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1825,2499,'sidebar','About Us'),(1826,2499,'header','yes'),(1827,2499,'footer',''),(1828,2499,'_edit_lock','1537763483:11'),(1829,2500,'_edit_last','11'),(1830,2500,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1831,2500,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(1832,2500,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Eastside Community School Board of Directors</h1>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Founding Board of Directors is an initiative group of parents and faculty who formed the new corporation, Eastside Community School.  The intention of the initiative is to embody a three-fold structure, balancing cultures from the basis of the three-pillar model of Waldorf school governance.  </span>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><b>Founding Board Members (Voting)</b></td>\r\n<td style=\"vertical-align: middle;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Griffith Owen, President</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Boris Bobrov, Vice President</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Anneliese Johnson, Secretary</span>\r\nDan Holsclaw, <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Treasurer</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Brandon Dudley</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Daniel Goldschmidt</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Andy Hartpence</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Lisa O’Connell</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><b>Board Advisor Seats (Non-Voting)</b></td>\r\n<td style=\"vertical-align: middle;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Faculty Advisor #1  Mary Spurgin</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Faculty Advisor #2</span></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Emma Goldschmidt\r\nFaculty Advisor #3</span></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Annette Campana </span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h1>Eastside Community School Volunteers</h1>\r\nThe Eastside Community School has been co-created by an engaged parent and faculty community. Whatever your talents and regardless of the amount of time you have to commit, we\'d love to have you join our community of volunteers. For more information, email<a href=\"mailto:info@eastsidecommunityschool.org\"> info@eastsidecommunityschool.org</a>.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_hr class=\'default\' height=\'50\' shadow=\'no-shadow\' position=\'center\']\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<a title=\"Board Log-In\" href=\"/board-log-in/\">Board Member Portal</a>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n'),(1833,2500,'layout',''),(1834,2500,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','9197f4b9da'),(1835,2500,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','About Us'),(1836,2500,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1837,2500,'sidebar','About Us'),(1838,2500,'header','yes'),(1839,2500,'footer',''),(1840,2500,'_edit_lock','1551852242:11'),(1841,2501,'_edit_last','8'),(1842,2501,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1843,2501,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active',''),(1844,2501,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','<h1>School Initiative Group</h1>\r\nThe Eastside Community School is being co-created by an engaged parent and faculty community. Whatever your talents and regardless of the amount of time you have to commit, we\'d love to have you join our community of volunteers. For more information, email <a href=\"mailto:tcsinitiative@gmail.com\">tcsinitiative@gmail.com</a>.'),(1845,2501,'layout',''),(1846,2501,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','1b13eedcda'),(1847,2501,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','About Us'),(1848,2501,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1849,2501,'sidebar','About Us'),(1850,2501,'header','yes'),(1851,2501,'footer',''),(1852,2501,'_edit_lock','1535400705:8'),(1853,2502,'_edit_last','8'),(1854,2502,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1855,2502,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(1856,2502,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_two_third first]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Alumni: Stay In Touch</h1>\r\nOnce you’ve been a part of Three Cedars and the Eastside Community School, you’re always part of our community. And we are always interested in knowing how our community members are living, working, and thriving.\r\n\r\nReconnect with us by submitting the form. When you do, you’ll have the opportunity to take part in events and receive updates about current news and activities at Eastside Community School.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n[contact-form-7 id=\"3985\" title=\"Alumni Stay In Touch Form\"]\r\n<p class=\"mice\"><em>Note: We don\'t share names and emails. Your contact information will be kept confidential.\r\n</em></p>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[/av_two_third]'),(1857,2502,'layout',''),(1858,2502,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','6196187984'),(1859,2502,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','About Us'),(1860,2502,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(1861,2502,'sidebar','About Us'),(1862,2502,'header','yes'),(1863,2502,'footer',''),(1864,2502,'_edit_lock','1552287863:11'),(1865,2503,'_edit_last','8'),(1866,2503,'_wp_page_template','default'),(1867,2503,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(39208,2503,'_avia_builder_shortcode_tree','a:3:{i:0;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:12:\"av_textblock\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:0;}i:1;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:12:\"av_textblock\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:1;}i:2;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:12:\"av_textblock\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:2;}}'),(39217,10106,'_wp_attached_file','2019/03/Early-Childhood-Teacher.pdf'),(39207,2503,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h1>Employment</h1>\r\n<h2>A Dynamic Place to Learn and to Work</h2>\r\nEastside Community School honors teachers’ commitment to Anthroposophy and focuses on students’ well-being, while being committed to sustainable growth and success as a dynamic learning institution. We offer a PreK-8 program. For more information, email <a href=\"mailto:info@eastsidecommunityschool.org\">info@eastsidecommunityschool.org</a>. <!--You can find employment opportunities at Eastside Community School <a href=\"http://www.seattlewaldorf.org/contact/\">here</a>.-->\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<h2>A Setting as Rich and Varied as Our Programs</h2>\r\nEastside Community School is located on 5.5 wooded acres in Bellevue, WA, across Lake Washington from Seattle. Our location is perfectly placed for you to explore and appreciate the renowned beauty and diversity of the Pacific Northwest, from outdoor and wilderness recreational opportunities on land, mountain, and sea to a full array of civic and cultural events.\r\n<h2>Current Openings</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888learn/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Kindergarten-Assistant-Teacher.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Immediate Opening for Kindergarten Assistant Teacher</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888learn/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Extended-Day.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Immediate Opening for Early Childhood Extended Day Assistant </a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888learn/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/ECS_Middle_School_Team_Teacher-1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">M</a><a href=\"http://localhost:8888learn/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/ECS_Middle_School_Team_Teacher-1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">iddle School Team Teacher</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888learn/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Early-Childhood-Teacher.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Early Childhood Teacher</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888learn/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Early-Childhood-Extended-Day-Assistant-1-1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Early Childhood Extended Day Assistant</a>\r\n<h2>How to Apply</h2>\r\nPlease complete the <a href=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/learn/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Employment-Application-Form.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Employment Application Form</a> and submit it with your résumé (which includes education, job history, and professional references) to <a href=\"mailto:jobs@eastsidecommunityschool.org\">jobs@eastsidecommunityschool.org</a>.\r\n\r\n<!--Eastside Community School is working to renew its membership with the Association of Waldorf Schools of North America (AWSNA) and the Northwest Association of Independent Schools (NWAIS).-->\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\n<a href=\"http://get.adobe.com/reader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Get Adobe Reader</a>\r\nTo use fill-able PDF forms, please save the form on your computer, and open in Adobe Reader.\r\n\r\n<!--Eastside Community School is working to renew its membership with the Association of Waldorf Schools of North America (AWSNA) and the Northwest Association of Independent Schools (NWAIS).-->\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n'),(38476,9621,'_wp_attached_file','2018/06/ECS_Spanish_Teacher.pdf'),(37996,9141,'_wp_page_template','default'),(37997,9141,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active',''),(37998,9141,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','<h1>School Initiative Group</h1>\r\nThe Eastside Community School is being co-created by an engaged parent and faculty community. Whatever your talents and regardless of the amount of time you have to commit, we\'d love to have you join our community of volunteers. For more information, email <a href=\"mailto:tcsinitiative@gmail.com\">tcsinitiative@gmail.com</a>.'),(26233,7268,'_wp_attached_file','2015/01/Audited-Financial-Statements-2013-14.pdf'),(26234,7268,'_edit_lock','1422024066:2'),(24690,7017,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:273;s:6:\"height\";i:222;s:4:\"file\";