sophy. This class aids young children in building a secure bridge to their expanding world and nourishes parents in their work.\r\n\r\nDuring Parent & Child class, parents and children work and play together, prepare a snack, celebrate the seasons, and enjoy songs, stories, and hand gesture games.\r\n\r\nRegular parent evenings are held throughout the school year with all early childhood families where we further explore the foundations of an early childhood experience inspired by Waldorf education.\r\n<h2>Daily Rhythm</h2>\r\nWe follow a rhythmical structure of work and imaginative play to develop skills for healthy social interaction. Each day includes time in our play yard to instill an appreciation of the natural world.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Arrival</li>\r\n 	<li>Indoor activity and play while parents engage in craft activity</li>\r\n 	<li>Inside circle with songs, finger games, movement, and verse</li>\r\n 	<li>Outdoor play in yard</li>\r\n 	<li>Good-bye</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2>Space Still Available.  Late enrollments will be prorated.</h2>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_toggle_container initial=\'2\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Session Dates and Times\' tags=\'\']\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 8px;\"><strong>Tuesday Program (9:30 a.m - 11:30 a.m.)</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 8px;\">Winter/Spring Session (20 Weeks)</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>January 8, 15, 22, 29</li>\r\n 	<li>February 5, 12, 26</li>\r\n 	<li>March 5, 12, 19, 26</li>\r\n 	<li>April 2, 9, 30</li>\r\n 	<li>May 7, 14, 21, 28</li>\r\n 	<li>June 4, 11</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 8px;\"><strong>Thursday Program (9:30 a.m - 11:30 a.m.)</strong></p>\r\nWinter Session (8 weeks)\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>January 31</li>\r\n 	<li>February 7, 14, 28</li>\r\n 	<li>March 7, 14, 21, 28</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSpring Session (8 weeks)\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>April 4, 11</li>\r\n 	<li>May 2, 9, 16, 23, 30</li>\r\n 	<li>June 6</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<!--\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 