'0\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Imagination\' tags=\'\']Young children are supported in their natural development by an emphasis on imagination as explored through play, purposeful activity, movement, social life, art and a rich tradition of oral storytelling, all provided in a warm and secure environment.\r\n\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Simple Play\' tags=\'\']\r\nThe kind of playful work in which children engage in the Waldorf classroom is very different from the media-saturated expectations generated by most modern toys and electronic games. We provide young children many opportunities for undirected play while guiding them in creating a healthy social group with their peers.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Rhythm\' tags=\'\']\r\n<o>Because a consistent, dependable daily rhythm provides a critical sense of security for a young child, activities are scheduled to follow the natural rhythms of a child’s day and year, balancing indoor and outdoor free play with more focused artistic and practical activities such as baking, painting, or crafts, and with circle time including rhymes, songs, and storytelling.\r\n\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Beauty\' tags=\'\']Our classrooms are designed to support a foundation of Waldorf teaching: the world is good and beautiful. Classrooms are pleasant and calm areas for working and playing, our toys and art supplies are created from natural materials, and our outdoor areas include playgrounds, grassy fields, and natural woods for magical adventures.\r\n\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Purposeful Activity\' tags=\'\']Young children begin school enthusiastic and excited to learn. Our activities prepare them for the challenges of elementary school subjects while nurturing and maintaining their enthusiasm:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Songs, stories and rhymes cultivate intimacy with language</li>\r\n	<li>Puppet shows and dramatic play strengthen memory and imagination</li>\r\n	<li>Counting games and rhythmic activities build a solid foundation for arithmetic skills</li>\r\n	<li>Painting and crafts help develop fine motor skills, coordination, and concentration</li>\r\n	<li>Vigorous play enhances concentration as it develops gross motor skills, proprioception, and vitality</li>\r\n	<li>Seasonal and outdoor activities foster understanding of the natural world</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]\r\n\r\n'),(24543,6977,'layout',''),(24544,6977,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_update_nonce','ad67954573'),(24545,6977,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name','Programs and Curriculum : Early Childhood'),(24546,6977,'simplepagesidebars_page_sidebar_name_new',''),(24547,6977,'sidebar','Programs and Curriculum : Early Childhood'),(24548,6977,'header','yes'),(24549,6977,'footer',''),(24550,6977,'_edit_lock','1539135875:8'),(24551,6977,'_sidebar_name','Programs and Curriculum : Early Childhood'),(24552,6977,'_avia_builder_shortcode_tree','a:2:{i:0;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:12:\"av_textblock\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:0;}i:1;a:3:{s:3:\"tag\";s:19:\"av_toggle_container\";s:7:\"content\";a:0:{}s:5:\"index\";i:1;}}'),(24553,6977,'header_title_bar',''),(24554,6977,'_dp_original','2483'),(24555,2483,'header_transparency',''),(24556,2483,'_avia_hide_featured_image','0'),(24575,6982,'_edit_last','2'),(24576,6982,'_wp_page_template','default'),(24577,6982,'_aviaLayoutBuilder_active','active'),(24578,6982,'_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData','[av_textblock]\r\n<h1>Early Childhood Curriculum Overview</h1>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_table purpose=\'tabular\' caption=\'\' responsive_styling=\'avia_responsive_table\']\r\n[av_row row_style=\'avia-heading-row\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\'][/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Parent-Tot[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Preschool [/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Kindergarten[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\']<strong>Daily \r\nRhythm</strong>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>Arrival</li>\r\n	<li>Indoor play and parent craft activity</li>\r\n	<li>Inside Circle:\r\nSongs, finger games, movement, verse and puppet play</li>\r\n	<li>Outdoor play in yard</li>\r\n	<li>Goodbye</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>Arrival and daily activity</li>\r\n	<li>Indoor play</li>\r\n	<li>Circle:\r\nStory, songs and finger games</li>\r\n	<li>Snack</li>\r\n	<li>Walk</li>\r\n	<li>Outdoor play</li>\r\n	<li>Story</li>\r\n	<li>Departure for half day students</li>\r\n	<li>Lunch, rest/nap and afternoon program for full day students</li>\r\n<ul>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>Arrival and daily activity</li>\r\n	<li>Indoor play</li>\r\n	<li>Circle:\r\nStory, songs and finger games</li>\r\n	<li>Snack</li>\r\n	<li>Walk</li>\r\n	<li>Outdoor play</li>\r\n	<li>Story</li>\r\n	<li>Departure for half day students</li>\r\n	<li>Lunch, rest/nap and afternoon program for full day students</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\']<strong>Weekly Activities</strong>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']N/A[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>Vegetable chopping</li>\r\n	<li>Watercolor painting</li>\r\n	<li>Drawing</li>\r\n	<li>Sewing</li>\r\n	<li>Finger knitting</li>\r\n	<li>Grain grinding</li>\r\n	<li>Bread baking</li>\r\n	<li>Woodworking</li>\r\n	<li>Gardening</li>\r\n	<li>Cleaning</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>Vegetable chopping</li>\r\n	<li>Watercolor painting</li>\r\n	<li>Drawing</li>\r\n	<li>Sewing</li>\r\n	<li>Finger knitting</li>\r\n	<li>Grain grinding</li>\r\n	<li>Bread baking</li>\r\n	<li>Woodworking</li>\r\n	<li>Gardening</li>\r\n	<li>Cleaning</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\']<strong>Seasonal Rhythm</strong>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Craft and circle activities, chosen to reflect the season[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Crafts and circle activities, chosen to reflect the season, along with seasonal celebrations: Michaelmas, Lantern Walk, and Spring Parade[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Crafts and circle activities, chosen to reflect the season, along with seasonal celebrations: Michaelmas, Lantern Walk, and Spring Parade[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\']<strong>Age Range</strong>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Ages birth to 4 years old, with a parent or caregiver[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']For children ages 2-1/2 to 4 years old. Must be 2-1/2 by Sept 1.[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Ages 5 – 6 years old. Must be 5 by Sept 1.  (Younger children may be admitted, pending teacher’s assessment.) Mixed-age program.[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\']<strong>Schedule</strong>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>One class per week</li>\r\n	<li>9 classes per session</li>\r\n	<li>Saturdays\r\n10 am – 12 pm</li>\r\n	<li>See <a href=\"http://threecedarswaldorf.org/learn/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/TCWS_ParentTot_RegForm_2014-15.pdf\">registration form</a> for dates</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>2-day program: Th & F</li>\r\n	<li>3-day program: M, T, W</li>\r\n	<li>5-day program: M – F</li>\r\n	<li>Choice of half or full day</li>\r\n	<li>Half Day: 8:00 am – 12:00 pm</li>\r\n	<li>Full Day: 8:00 am – 2:45 pm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']<ul>\r\n	<li>5 days per week</li>\r\n	<li>Choice of half or full day</li>\r\n	<li>Half Day: 8:00 am – 12:00 pm</li>\r\n	<li>Full Day: 8:00 am – 2:45 pm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/av_cell][/av_row]\r\n[av_row row_style=\'\'][av_cell col_style=\'avia-desc-col\']<strong>Extended Care</strong>[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Not available[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Available from dismissal time until 6:00 pm, for full day students only.[/av_cell][av_cell col_style=\'\']Available from dismissal time until 6:00